query: What is the submission process for research papers?
output: For the Ph.D. Symposium track, papers should be single-authored by the student and contain the statement of the problem being addressed, an outline of the planned methodology, contributions made so far, and the work lying ahead. For the Industry and Applications Track, manuscripts must be prepared in accordance with the IEEE format and submitted to the ICDE 2023 submission website. Only electronic submissions in PDF format will be considered. Papers that do not follow the guidelines or are not within the scope of topics relevant to ICDE will be desk rejected. Papers cannot be under review for any other conference or journal during the time it is considered for ICDE 2023, and should be substantially different from any previously published work. Each submission must include all author names and affiliations. Changes to the author list after paper acceptance are not permitted unless explained via email to the industrial track chairs. All accepted papers will appear in the proceedings. Any paper from which none of the authors attend to present will be subject to removal from IEEE Xplore.
